it was like something in a horror movie 
9yearold jessica short was visiting a street festival when she 
was grabbed suddenly from behind and stabbed to death by an escaped 
mental patient as her mother and dozens of others watched 
a week later the story still haunts connecticut kept on 
newspapers front pages by a second escape from the same hospital 
and by troubling questions about security at the states mental 
institutions 
mental health officials who at first protested that they were 
running hospitals not prisons have now moved to tighten security 
around the states small population of criminally insane mental 
patients 
but the new security has done little to comfort residents and 
officials in middletown who have lived for years in an uneasy 
peace with connecticut valley hospital a 120yearold brick 
complex that houses many of the states 172 criminally insane 
patients 
people who walk with their children on main street in 
middletown hold their children closer now because of the 
incident said mayor sebastian garafalo 
on july 28 david peterson a paranoid schizophrenic walked 
away from the hospital where he was confined last year after 
attacking a neighbor he stabbed jessica to death apparently 
choosing her at random from among fairgoers on a crowded sidewalk 
i absolutely blame the hospital said vincent amato a 
middletown merchant who else could you blame they were charged 
by society to take care of this man who had a problem they 
failed 
some mental health workers worry the incident has bred what one 
