when the plane carrying presidential aide 
steve studdert tried to land on africas serengeti plains it first 
had to buzz the landing area to chase off a couple hundred 
wildebeests 
that accomplished he recalled none of the passengers dared 
deplane until some feasting lions polished off the dinner they had 
felled nearby 
the episode en route to an energy meeting in kenya was just one 
of many on studderts 5 millionmile odyssey searching out the 
perfect image for three presidents 
he went by air in everything from f16 fighters to blimps he 
went by sea in everything from submarines to tugboats and he went 
by land in everything from fire trucks to ambulances 
but after surveying the sights from the shipyards of poland to 
the wild creatures of the serengeti the white house advance guru 
is hanging it up at the white house to point his trusty jeep 
homeward to the sleepy town of highland utah 
studdert formally the assistant to president bush for special 
activities and initiatives said he wants to leave government for 
a more quiet life and denies reports he is planning to run for 
governor of utah 
its just time he said to spend his time on things other than 
boating down the mississippi to plan a presidential tour of flood 
devastation or riding the rails across ohio on a campaign whistle 
stop 
but he is not shy about recalling his behindthescenes role in 
shaping years of presidential level memories 
what was wonderful for me as i look at the most recent europe 
trip i realize that 45 days before the president went there i was 
there studdert said in an interview i stood in an empty 
church in leiden i stood in an empty square in gdansk in my 
minds eye i saw what i hoped could be what a wonderful feeling it 
was to go with the president and see it happen 
what happened was 25000 poles packed into the square in gdansk 
cheering an american president what happened was several hundred 
dutch sitting quietly in a church to hear an american president 
