the 21 activists who publicly identified themselves and said 
they would not abide by their police orders have been restricted 
since their release from detention earlier this year 
the restrictions vary but most activists are required to be at 
home from dusk to dawn and are not allowed to attend meetings where 
the government is criticized 
no uniformed police were present 
the government has released almost 1000 detainees since they 
went on a hunger strike in january however about half have been 
placed under restriction orders according to human rights groups 
an estimated 30000 people almost all black have been detained 
without charge for varying lengths of time under the 3yearold 
state of emergency although only a few dozen currently are held 
