<TEXT>
fruehauf corp is no more after changing 
its name to kh corp as part of the automotive parts 
manufacturers sale of its truck trailer and maritime businesses 
the company completed the name change at the close of business 
friday it said in a news release from its suburban detroit 
headquarters the name change was required under terms of the july 
14 sale of its subsidiaries 
on may 5 torontobased varity corp agreed to buy fruehauf for 
436 million and 555 million shares of varity stock 
the name change wont affect that takeover kh said in a news 
release the takeover is expected to be completed by the end of 
september said robert siefert khs president 
in march a division of terex corp agreed to buy freuhaufs 
truck trailer and maritime manufacturing operations for about 233 
million 
kh now principally serves as a holding company for kelseyhayes 
co a maker of aluminum and steel wheels brake parts and other 
car and truck components 
kh will trade on the new york stock exchange under the ticker 
symbol kh the company said 
fruehauf encountered severe financial difficulties after a 
leveraged buyout in 1986 to avoid a hostile takeover left the 
company heavily indebted 
